Install Guide


Commands


Arch Install


Connect to a network

iwctl

device list
station device scan
station device get-networks 
station device connect SSID
Exit
ping google.com 

Update Time

timedatectl set-timezone Asia/Karachi


Partitioning

lsblk 
Fdisk -l
cfdisk /dev/nvme0n1
mkfs.ext4 /dev/nvme0n1p*

Mounting

mount /dev/nvme0n1p* /mnt
mkdir /mnt/home 
mount /dev/nvme0n1p* /mnt/home


Install Base System 

pacstrap -i /mnt base base-devel linux linux-lts linux-headers linux-firmware intel-ucode sudo networkmanager nano git neofetch dhcpcd ntfs-3g 

Fstab

genfstab -U /mnt >> /mnt/etc/fstab

ArchChroot

arch-chroot /mnt
passwd 
useradd -m aliammar
passwd aliammar 
usermod-aG wheel,power,storage aliammar
EDITOR=nano visudo 

nano /etc/locale.gen
locale-gen
echo LANG=en_GB.UTF-8 > /etc/locale.conf
export LANG=en_GB.UTF-8

echo RAZER-A > /etc/hostname 
nano /etc/hosts

127.0.0.1    localhost 
::1               localhost
127.0.1.1     RAZER-A.localdomain   localhost

ln-sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Karachi /etc/localtime

hwclock --systohc

Bootloader 

mkdir /boot/efi 
mount /dev/nvme0n1p1/ /boot/efi
pacman -S grub efibootmgr dosfstools mtools os-prober 

nano /etc/default/grub
grub-install —target=x86_64-efi —bootloader-id=ArchLinux —recheck

grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg 


systemctl enable dhcpcd.service
systemctl enable NetworkManager.service
exit 
reboot 

nmcli device wifi list
nmcli device wifi connect SSID_or_BSSID password password

Base System Installed

KDE Install
sudo pacman-S xorg xorg-init xterm plasma plasma-desktop plasma-wayland-session kde-applications kdeplasma-addons ssdm 

sudo nano ~/.xinitrc     exec startkde 
sudo systemctl enable sddm.service

Gnome Install 

sudo Pacman -S gnome

